Cameron Orders Independent Probe of News of the World Hacking Allegations

-- B y   G o n z a l o   V i n a
-- 
2011-07-08T08:47:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/cameron-orders-independent-probe-of-news-of-the-world-hacking-allegations.html
Prime Minister  David Cameron  said
that there have been “illegal” practices at the News of the
World and possibly other newspapers and that there will be a
full judicial inquiry. He was speaking at a news conference in
 London  today.  “What we can get started we will get started,” Cameron
said. Everything that happened will be investigated.’’  Cameron said witnesses will be questioned under oath. He
said he plans a second inquiry into the “culture, the ethics
and practices” of the British press.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gonzalo Vina in London at 
 gvina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Eddie Buckle at 
 ebuckle@bloomberg.net  